Mark 08-Sep-19 12:37 PM
Okay boys here's the procedure for hosting scrimmages: ONE PING PER ROUND. ^ This ping would be for ready up. We will not be pinging for the link, simply to keep the complaints of pings to a minimum. As of now, the only game modes we're going to be hosting will be Flood and Normal BR. Circles cannot be performed without an excess of pings, and the entire goal of this new rendition of scrims is to keep the pings to a minimum. The current schedule for hosting scrims is as follows: (subject to change) Wednesday: 3:00 PM EST - 6:00 PM EST (7:00 PM GMT - 10:00 PM GMT) Friday: 2:00 PM EST - 6:00 PM EST (6:00 PM GMT - 10:00 PM GMT) Saturday: 10:00 AM EST - 6:00 PM EST (2:00 PM GMT - 10:00 PM GMT) (this is the largest window/day for hosting scrims, a total of 7 hours of scrim hosting time, see note at bottom for why I subtracted an hour) Sunday: 12:00 PM EST - 6:00 PM EST (4:00 PM GMT - 10:00 PM GMT) Scrimmages cannot be hosted for more then 8 hours without at least a 1 hour break period. This is to prevent constant pings. You may notice more restrictions on the weekdays due to kids being in school. We want to keep things reasonable.(edited)
Saturday is by far the best day to host scrims, as in the future it may be update days. You can start scrims on Saturday as early as 10:00 AM EST.
